<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
  <title>PAIN DURING INTERCOURSE (DYSPAREUNIA)</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="Case_sheet_styles.css">
  <link id="dark-styles" rel="alternate stylesheet" title="dark" href="Case_sheet_styles_dark.css">
  <script src="https://www.youtube.com/iframe_api"></script>
</head>
<body>
  <button id="theme-toggle" title="Toggle dark mode">🌙 Dark Mode</button>

  <div>
    <h3>COMPLAINT: PAIN DURING INTERCOURSE (DYSPAREUNIA)</h3>

    <!-- S: Site -->
    <div class="point">
      <div class="point-content">
        <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Site (Superficial vs Deep)</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="gynob"><b>Superficial / entry pain:</b> at the vaginal opening, vulva, or perineum.
            <ul>
              <li class="infectious"><b>Infection:</b> Thrush (Candida), Herpes, genital warts.</li>
              <li class="gynob">Atrophic vaginitis (menopause &rarr; low oestrogen, dryness).</li>
              <li class="gynob psychiatric">Vaginismus &ndash; involuntary muscle spasm preventing entry.</li>
              <li class="gynob">Vulvodynia / vestibulodynia (chronic nerve pain at the vestibule).</li>
              <li class="trauma">Scarring/trauma: episiotomy scars, perineal tears after childbirth.</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li class="gynob"><b>Deep / collision pain:</b> felt high in the vagina or pelvis with deep penetration.
            <ul>
              <li class="gynob">Endometriosis &ndash; classic deep dyspareunia.</li>
              <li class="gynob">PID / adhesions (chronic pelvic inflammatory disease).</li>
              <li class="gynob">Fibroids / ovarian cysts or other space-occupying lesions.</li>
              <li class="git">Bowel issues: IBS, constipation, rectal pathology.</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li class="General">Unilateral / bilateral pelvic pain?</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <span class="verbal">"I know this can be difficult to discuss, but to help you I need to know exactly where the pain is &mdash; is it right at the entrance when penetration starts, or do you feel it deep inside your tummy/pelvis?"</span>
    </div>

    <!-- O: Onset -->
    <div class="point">
      <div class="point-content">
        <span class="description"><strong>O</strong>: Onset</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="General">When did the pain with sex first start?</li>
          <li class="General">Sudden onset (after infection, trauma, new partner, childbirth, surgery) vs gradual.</li>
          <li class="gynob">Primary (pain from first intercourse attempt) vs Secondary (started after a period of painless sex).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <span class="verbal">"Have you always had pain during sex, or did it start after a time when sex was comfortable?"</span>
    </div>

    <!-- D: Duration -->
    <div class="point">
      <div class="point-content">
        <span class="description"><strong>D</strong>: Duration</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="General">How long has this been an issue (months / years)?</li>
          <li class="General">Does the pain last only during penetration, or continue afterwards?</li>
          <li class="General">Acute onset with infection or trauma vs chronic pain over months/years (e.g. endometriosis, vulvodynia).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <span class="verbal">"How long have you been experiencing this pain with intercourse?"</span>
    </div>

    <!-- A/R: Aggravating & Relieving Factors -->
    <div class="point">
      <div class="point-content">
        <span class="description"><strong>A/R</strong>: Aggravating &amp; Relieving Factors</span>
        <ul>
          <li><b>AGGRAVATING:</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="gynob">Penetration at the entrance vs deep thrusting.</li>
              <li class="gynob">Certain positions (e.g. deep penetration from behind).</li>
              <li class="gynob">Lack of lubrication / vaginal dryness (menopause, breastfeeding, medications).</li>
              <li class="gynob">Immediately before or during menstruation (endometriosis, adenomyosis).</li>
              <li class="infectious">Active vaginal infection or discharge (thrush, BV, PID, STIs).</li>
              <li class="gynob">After pelvic surgery, childbirth, episiotomy, perineal tear.</li>
              <li class="gynob">Tampon use, cycling, tight clothing aggravating vulval/vestibular pain.</li>
              <li class="psychiatric">High anxiety, fear, past trauma worsening muscle tension (vaginismus).</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><b>RELIEVING:</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="gynob">Lubricants, longer foreplay, change of position.</li>
              <li class="gynob">Shallower penetration, avoiding certain positions.</li>
              <li class="General">Pain-free with self-stimulation but painful with penetration (points to mechanical/penetrative causes).</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <span class="verbal">"Are there certain positions or times when it is worse? Does using lubricant or changing position help at all?"</span>
    </div>

    <!-- C: Character -->
    <div class="point">
      <div class="point-content">
        <span class="description"><strong>C</strong>: Character / Type</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="gynob"><b>Burning / stinging</b> at the entrance (vulvodynia, dermatoses, infections, fissures).</li>
          <li class="gynob"><b>Sharp, stabbing, "hitting a wall"</b> on penetration (vaginismus, hymenal ring, atrophic vaginitis).</li>
          <li class="gynob"><b>Deep aching / cramping</b> in pelvis with deep thrusting (endometriosis, PID, ovarian cysts, fibroids, adhesions).</li>
          <li class="gynob">Superficial vs deep pain helps localise cause.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <span class="verbal">"Is it more of a burning at the entrance, or a deeper ache or cramp inside your pelvis?"</span>
    </div>

    <!-- R: Radiation -->
    <div class="point">
      <div class="point-content">
        <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Radiation</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="General">Does the pain spread to the lower abdomen, back, or thighs?
            <ul>
              <li class="gynob">To back or rectum &rarr; think endometriosis in pouch of Douglas or deep pelvic disease.</li>
              <li class="gynob">Down the legs &rarr; large fibroids or cysts pressing on nerves.</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <span class="verbal">"Does the pain stay in one spot, or does it travel to your tummy, back, or legs?"</span>
    </div>

    <!-- A: Associated Symptoms -->
    <div class="point">
      <div class="point-content">
        <span class="description"><strong>A</strong>: Associated Symptoms</span>
        <ul>
          <li><b>GYNAE:</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="gynob">Abnormal vaginal bleeding (intermenstrual, post-coital, heavy periods).</li>
              <li class="gynob">Pelvic pain outside intercourse (endometriosis, PID, ovarian cysts).</li>
              <li class="gynob">Vaginal dryness, itching, burning.</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><b>DISCHARGE / INFECTION:</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="infectious">Change in discharge (color, odour, consistency) &rarr; thrush (curdy), BV (fishy), trichomonas, gonorrhoea, chlamydia.</li>
              <li class="infectious">Fever, pelvic tenderness (PID, tubo-ovarian abscess).</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><b>URINARY:</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="nephro">Dysuria, urgency, frequency, haematuria (UTI vs interstitial cystitis).</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><b>BOWEL:</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="git">Pain with defaecation, constipation, diarrhoea, rectal pain (endometriosis, IBS).</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li><b>SEXUAL / PSYCHOLOGICAL:</b>
            <ul>
              <li class="psychiatric">Low libido, fear of intercourse, relationship strain.</li>
              <li class="psychiatric">History of sexual trauma or assault (ask sensitively if appropriate).</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <span class="verbal">"Any unusual bleeding, discharge, bladder or bowel symptoms, or is this pain affecting how you feel about sex or your relationship?"</span>
    </div>

    <!-- P: Pattern (Timing / Frequency) -->
    <div class="point">
      <div class="point-content">
        <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Pattern (Timing / Frequency)</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="gynob">Every attempt at intercourse vs occasional episodes.</li>
          <li class="gynob">Relation to menstrual cycle (worse around periods or mid-cycle).</li>
          <li class="General">New partner vs long-term partner? Any change when using condoms / lubrication?</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <span class="verbal">"Is it every time you have sex, or only sometimes? Does it change with your cycle or partner?"</span>
    </div>

    <!-- P: Progression -->
    <div class="point">
      <div class="point-content">
        <span class="description"><strong>P</strong>: Progression</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="General">Stable, gradually worsening, or improving over time?</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <span class="verbal">"Has this pain been getting worse, better, or staying about the same?"</span>
    </div>

    <!-- E: Effect on life -->
    <div class="point">
      <div class="point-content">
        <span class="description"><strong>E</strong>: Effect on Life</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="gynob">Avoidance of intercourse or intimacy.</li>
          <li class="psychiatric">Impact on mood, self-esteem, relationship stress.</li>
          <li class="General">Effect on overall quality of life and sense of safety/comfort in sexual situations.</li>
          <li class="gynob">Fertility concerns if trying to conceive (avoiding or unable to complete intercourse).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <span class="verbal">"How has this affected your sex life, mood, or relationship?"</span>
    </div>

    <!-- R: Red Flags -->
    <div class="point">
      <div class="point-content">
        <span class="description"><strong>R</strong>: Red Flags</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="oncology emergency"><b>Post-coital bleeding (PCB):</b> cervical ectropion, polyps, dysplasia or carcinoma.</li>
          <li class="oncology emergency"><b>Post-menopausal bleeding (PMB):</b> endometrial hyperplasia/cancer until proven otherwise.</li>
          <li class="oncology">Unexplained weight loss, pelvic mass (consider malignancy).</li>
          <li class="infectious emergency">Fever, severe pelvic pain, purulent discharge (PID, tubo-ovarian abscess).</li>
          <li class="obstetric emergency">Possible pregnancy with severe pain/bleeding (ectopic pregnancy) if of reproductive age.</li>
          <li class="psychiatric emergency">Any disclosure or concern about sexual assault or coercion.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <span class="verbal">"I need to ask some safety questions &ndash; any bleeding after sex, fevers with pain, or anything that has made you feel unsafe or forced in sexual situations?"</span>
    </div>

    <!-- S: Severity / Scale -->
    <div class="point">
      <div class="point-content">
        <span class="description"><strong>S</strong>: Severity / Scale</span>
        <ul>
          <li class="General">0&ndash;10 pain score during intercourse.</li>
          <li class="gynob">Can intercourse be completed, or is it stopped early every time because of pain?</li>
          <li class="psychiatric">Distress/impact scale (e.g. 0&ndash;10 how upsetting or distressing this problem is).</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <span class="verbal">"On a scale of 0 to 10, how bad is the pain during sex? Are you able to continue, or do you have to stop?"</span>
    </div>

  </div>

  <script src="theme-toggle.js"></script>
